Braised Short Ribs Recipe. 5 pounds bone-in beef short rib, seasoned with salt and pepper
3 Tbsp avocado oil
2 Celery stalks, chopped
2 Medium carrots, peeled, chopped
1 Large onion, chopped
3 Tbsp all-purpose flour
2 Tbsp tomato paste
1 (750 ml) bottle dry red wine
2 Sprigs rosemary
4 Sprigs oregano
6 Sprigs thyme
3 Dried bay leaves
1 Large head of garlic, chopped in half
32 Oz package low-salt beef stock
Chives to garnish
Preheat oven to 350°. Season short ribs with salt and pepper. Heat oil in a large oven safe pot over medium-high. Brown short ribs, about
2-3 minutes on each side. Remove short ribs and set aside.
Add celery, carrots, and onions to the pot and cook over medium-high heat. Stir often until onions are browned,
about 5 minutes. Add flour and tomato paste. Stir continuously, until well combined and a dark red color (about 2-3 minutes). Stir in wine and add short ribs. Bring to a boil. Then lower heat to medium and simmer until wine is reduced by half, about 25 minutes. Add rosemary, oregano, thyme, bay leaves, and garlic. Stir in beef stock and add salt and pepper to taste. Then bring to a boil, cover, and transter to oven.
Cook until short ribs are tender, about 4 hours. Serve with mashed potatoes and broccolini.Top with sauce and chives and enjoy! #food #foodie #dance #recipes

California Burrito 🌯 Recipe
Skirt steak
Large tortillas
Sour cream
Pepper jack cheese, shredded
Cheddar cheese, shredded

Steak Marinade:
2 Tsp Black pepper
11/2 Tbsp Salt
2 Tsp Cumin
3 Tsp Paprika
2 Tsp Garlic powder
2 Tsp Chili pepper
2 Tsp Onion powder
2 Tbsp Worcestershire sauce
1/2 a large Orange, juiced
1 Lime, juiced
2 Tbsp avocado oil
-Cut skirt steak into 2 or 3 pieces. Add all ingredients to a bowl and let marinate for about 2 hours. Cook in a skillet on high heat for 6-8 minutes on each side (or to your preferred doneness).

Fries:
1-2 Russet potatoes, skinned and sliced into even strips
Frying oil
Finishing salt
-After potatoes are skinned and sliced, add them to a bowl of ice water until you’re ready to fry. Add oil to a pan and heat until temperature reaches 350°F. Fry for 4 minutes. Remove and place on a rimmed baking sheet. Increase oil temperature to 375°F. When oil is ready, add fries back into the pan and fry for an additional 3-4 minutes, until golden brown. Toss in a bowl with finishing salt.

Guacamole:
3 Avocados
1/4 Cup red onions, chopped
1/3 Cup fresh cilantro, chopped
1/2 a Lime, juiced
1/4 Cup jalapeños, chopped
Slat and pepper to taste
-Combine ingredients in a bowl.

Tomato Salsa:
2 Roma tomatoes
1/3 Cup onion, chopped
1/3 Cup cilantro, chopped
1/4 Cup jalapeños, chopped
Salt and pepper to taste
1/2 Lime, juiced
1/2 Lemon, juiced
-Combine ingredients in a bowl.
Create burrito by adding a layer of guacamole, sour cream, steak, fries, cheese, and salsa to the tortilla. Roll into a burrito and toast outside if desired. Enjoy!
#foodie #dance #recipe #californiaburrito #food

One of my favorites Stuffed French Toast 🫐 🍓. Recipe
Challah bread, cut 1 - 1 1/2 inch thick
Filling:
8 Oz cream cheese, room temperature
1/4 Cup sour cream
34 Cup powdered sugar
2 Tsp vanilla extract
1/2 Lemon zest
-Strawberry Topping:
8 oz strawberries
3 Tablespoons sugar
French toast batter:
3/4 Cup whole milk
1/2 Cup heavy cream
1 Tsp vanilla extract
3 Eggs
2 Egg yolks
1 Tsp ground cinnamon
1/8 Tsp ground nutmeg
1/2 Tsp sea salt
11/2 Tbsp dark brown sugar
-Cut challah bread 1-1.5 inch thick. Using a skewer, create a hole on the side of the bread without puncturing through the other side.
-In a medium bowl cut strawberries and add sugar. Mix and let sit for 15 minutes until it forms a syrup consistency. In a bowl combine the filling ingredients and mix until it forms a creamy consistency. In a separate bowl combine batter ingredients and mix.
Fill a baking bag with filling and squeeze into the holes in each piece of bread. Be carful not to over stuff because the bread can break.
-Transfer the french toast batter into a casserole dish and add each piece of bread in the mixture, coating all sides. Add about 2-3 Tbsp butter in a pan and cook toast for about 3-4 minutes on each side.
Serve with blueberries, sugared strawberries, syrup, and powdered sugar. Enjoy!
